    <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>200g spaghetti</li>
        <li>100g pancetta</li>
        <li>50g pecorino cheese</li>
        <li>2 large eggs</li>
        <li>Black pepper</li>
        <li>Salt</li>
        <li>Olive oil</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>General instructions:</h3>
    
    <ol>
        <li>Cook the spaghetti in salted boiling water until al dente.</li>
        <li>In a pan, cook the pancetta in a little olive oil until crispy.</li>
        <li>In a bowl, whisk together eggs and grated pecorino cheese.</li>
        <li>Drain the spaghetti and add it to the pan with pancetta.</li>
        <li>Remove from heat and quickly stir in the egg mixture to create a creamy sauce.</li>
